Compare IP vs Peak

CAR+

# Load data
integrated.obj <- readRDS("integrated.obj.rds")

# Filter by Peak
integrated.obj.IP <- subset(x = integrated.obj, subset = Class1 == "CAR+")
all.genes <- rownames(integrated.obj.IP)
integrated.obj.IP <- ScaleData(integrated.obj.IP, features = all.genes)
Idents(integrated.obj.IP) <- integrated.obj.IP$Timepoint

DEG <- FindMarkers(integrated.obj.IP, ident.1 = c("IP"), ident.2 = c("Peak"), verbose = FALSE,
    min.pct = -Inf, logfc.threshold = -Inf, min.cells.feature = 1, min.cells.group = 1)

EnhancedVolcano(DEG, rownames(DEG), x = "avg_log2FC", y = "p_val_adj", pCutoff = 0.05,
    FCcutoff = 0.5, xlim = c(-2, 2), drawConnectors = TRUE)
## Warning: One or more p-values is 0. Converting to 10^-1 * current lowest
## non-zero p-value...
## Warning: ggrepel: 408 unlabeled data points (too many overlaps). Consider
## increasing max.overlaps

# GSEA

DEG$clus <- ifelse(DEG$avg_log2FC > 0, "IP", "Peak")
DEG$avg_log2FC <- abs(DEG$avg_log2FC)

top100 <- DEG %>%
    group_by(clus) %>%
    top_n(n = 100, wt = avg_log2FC)
top100pval <- subset(top100, rowSums(top100[5] < 0.05) > 0)

DEG$gene <- rownames(DEG)
dfsample <- split(DEG$gene, DEG$clus)

dfsample$IP = bitr(dfsample$IP, fromType = "SYMBOL", toType = "ENTREZID", OrgDb = "org.Hs.eg.db")
## Warning in bitr(dfsample$IP, fromType = "SYMBOL", toType = "ENTREZID", OrgDb =
## "org.Hs.eg.db"): 20.84% of input gene IDs are fail to map...
dfsample$Peak = bitr(dfsample$Peak, fromType = "SYMBOL", toType = "ENTREZID", OrgDb = "org.Hs.eg.db")
## Warning in bitr(dfsample$Peak, fromType = "SYMBOL", toType = "ENTREZID", :
## 39.67% of input gene IDs are fail to map...
# do the same here, a line like below for each cluster
genelist <- list(IP = dfsample$IP$ENTREZID, Peak = dfsample$Peak$ENTREZID)

GOclusterplot <- compareCluster(geneCluster = genelist, fun = "enrichGO", ont = "BP",
    OrgDb = "org.Hs.eg.db")
DT::datatable(summary(GOclusterplot))
## Warning in summary(GOclusterplot): summary method to convert the object to
## data.frame is deprecated, please use as.data.frame instead.
dotplot(GOclusterplot, showCategory = 10)

KEGGclusterplot <- compareCluster(geneCluster = genelist, fun = "enrichKEGG")
DT::datatable(summary(KEGGclusterplot))
## Warning in summary(KEGGclusterplot): summary method to convert the object to
## data.frame is deprecated, please use as.data.frame instead.
dotplot(KEGGclusterplot, showCategory = 10)
